::KitKat::

She had a gut feeling something was wrong. She couldn't put her 
finger on it. Maybe it was the way they acted. Maybe it was the way 
they looked. But something wasn't right. She shook herhead thinking 
that leadership was making her paranoid. She smiled at 
herself. "Relax, not everyone is out to get you." she said aloud to 
herself.  She put the beacon unwittingly into a hip compartment. Her 
metal frame  blocked the signals tot he beacon box, it couldn't send 
or receive untill she took it out of the compartment.
